        "title": " fix(utils): make parseBooleanValue case-insensitive for custom lists and guard against malformed inputs",
        "body": "Summary\r\n\r\n   - Problem: parseBooleanValue was case-sensitive when using custom truthy/falsy lists and would throw a TypeError if those\r\n     options were provided as non-arrays (e.g., from untyped JSON or JS plugins).\r\n   - Why it matters: Prevents runtime crashes when processing malformed or untyped configuration data and makes custom boolean\r\n     parsing more robust and user-friendly.\r\n   - What changed: \r\n       - Added Array.isArray guards before mapping custom truthy/falsy lists.\r\n       - Implemented case-insensitivity for custom truthy/falsy overrides.\r\n       - Added comprehensive regression tests.\r\n   - What did NOT change: The core logic for default truthy/falsy values remains unchanged.\r\n\r\n  Change Type (select all)\r\n\r\n   - [x] Bug fix\r\n   - [ ] Feature\r\n   - [ ] Refactor required for the fix\r\n   - [ ] Docs\r\n   - [x] Security hardening\r\n   - [ ] Chore/infra\r\n\r\n  Scope (select all touched areas)\r\n\r\n   - [ ] Gateway / orchestration\r\n   - [ ] Skills / tool execution\r\n   - [ ] Auth / tokens\r\n   - [ ] Memory / storage\r\n   - [ ] Integrations\r\n   - [x] API / contracts\r\n   - [x] UI / DX\r\n   - [ ] CI/CD / infra\r\n\r\n  Linked Issue/PR\r\n\r\n   - Related #59535 (previous attempt)\r\n   - [x] This PR fixes a bug or regression\r\n\r\n  Root Cause (if applicable)\r\n\r\n   - Root cause: The implementation unconditionally called .map() on options.truthy and options.falsy, assuming they were always\r\n     arrays. It also missed case normalization for these custom strings.\r\n   - Missing detection / guardrail: Lack of type validation for runtime-injected options.\r\n   - Contributing context: Identified during Codex review of a previous merge.\r\n\r\n  Regression Test Plan (if applicable)\r\n\r\n   - Coverage level that should have caught this:\r\n     - [x] Unit test\r\n     - [ ] Seam / integration test\r\n     - [ ] End-to-end test\r\n     - [ ] Existing coverage already sufficient\r\n   - Target test or file: src/utils/utils-misc.test.ts\r\n   - Scenario the test should lock in:\r\n       - Passing non-array values to truthy/falsy options (should return undefined instead of crashing).\r\n       - Passing mixed-case custom strings (should match regardless of case).\r\n       - Passing non-string entries in custom lists.\r\n   - Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: Directly exercises the utility function with the problematic input shapes.\r\n\r\n  User-visible / Behavior Changes\r\n\r\n   - Custom boolean parsing via parseBooleanValue is now case-insensitive for custom lists.\r\n   - Malformed configuration for custom truthy/falsy lists will no longer crash the process.\r\n\r\n  Diagram (if applicable)\r\n\r\n   1 Before:\r\n   2 parseBooleanValue(\"yes\", { truthy: \"YES\" }) -> TypeError: truthy.map is not a function\r\n   3\r\n   4 After:\r\n   5 parseBooleanValue(\"yes\", { truthy: \"YES\" }) -> undefined (graceful fail)\r\n   6 parseBooleanValue(\"yes\", { truthy: [\"YES\"] }) -> true (case-insensitive match)\r\n\r\n  Security Impact (required)\r\n\r\n   - New permissions/capabilities? (No)\r\n   - Secrets/tokens handling changed? (No)\r\n   - New/changed network calls? (No)\r\n   - Command/tool execution surface changed? (No)\r\n   - Data access scope changed? (No)\r\n\r\n  Repro + Verification\r\n\r\n  Environment\r\n\r\n   - OS: darwin (macOS)\r\n   - Runtime: Node.js v23.11.0\r\n\r\n  Steps\r\n\r\n   1. Call parseBooleanValue(\"yes\", { truthy: \"YES\" })\r\n   2. Call parseBooleanValue(\"yes\", { truthy: [\"YES\"] })\r\n\r\n  Expected\r\n\r\n   1. Returns undefined (or previous behavior of ignoring invalid option).\r\n   2. Returns true.\r\n\r\n  Actual\r\n\r\n   1. Threw TypeError: truthy.map is not a function.\r\n   2. Returned undefined (case-sensitive mismatch).\r\n\r\n  Evidence\r\n\r\n   - [x] Failing test/log before + passing after (Verified via pnpm exec vitest run src/utils/utils-misc.test.ts)\r\n\r\n  Human Verification (required)\r\n\r\n   - Verified scenarios: Malformed options (string, object), mixed-case custom matches, non-string entries in lists.\r\n   - Edge cases checked: Empty strings, null values in lists, default behavior when no options are provided.\r\n   - What you did not verify: Integration with every single plugin that might use this (verified at the utility level).\r\n\r\n  Review Conversations\r\n\r\n   - [x] I replied to or resolved every bot review conversation I addressed in this PR.\r\n   - [x] I left unresolved only the conversations that still need reviewer or maintainer judgment.\r\n\r\n  Compatibility / Migration\r\n\r\n   - Backward compatible? (Yes)\r\n   - Config/env changes? (No)\r\n   - Migration needed? (No)\r\n\r\n  Risks and Mitigations\r\n\r\n   - None: The fix adds guards and increases flexibility without breaking existing functionality.",
